dialogue: Hi Alice! My name is Frosty :penguin: and I’m here to help you learn all about science:microscope:, verbal reasoning (GRE) :input_latin_uppercase:, and safety:hammer_and_wrench:!
I ask you questions, and you give me answers.
We will learn fun things together!
Good choice! Let's see what you know about safety!
If you know the answer, you can type it in and I'll help you to evaluate the answer :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes:
What should you NOT do when lowering a load?
Which of the following options is the right answer?

:keycap_1: Bend your knees
:keycap_2: Twist your body, keep the load close, and bend your knees
:keycap_3: Keep the load close to your body
:keycap_4: Twist your body
